Pour the @water{300%ml}(for the rice) into a #saucepan{} and bring to the boil. When
boiling, add @salt{0.25%tsp} and the @star anise{1}. Stir in the
@basmati rice{150%g}, lower the heat to medium and pop a lid on the pan. Leave
to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and
leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice
will continue to cook in its own steam).

Drain and pat your @firm tofu{280%g} dry with some #paper towel{}. Cut the block
in half lengthways and then cut each half into 6 cubes. In a #small bowl{}
combine the @plain flour{8%g}, a pinch of @Thai style spice mix{pinch}(careful it's hot!) and
season generously with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Toss the tofu cubes
through the flour ensuring that they are evenly coated.

Trim the @pak choi{1} then thinly slice widthways. Cut the @tenderstem broccoli{80%g} in half
widthways. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve
the @red chilli{1} lengthways, deseed then slice thinly. Zest the
@?lime{½} and cut into wedges. Trim the @spring onion{1} then slice thinly. Heat
a #large frying pan{} or #wok{} on a medium-high heat (no oil). When hot add the
@sesame seeds{15%g} and cook, stirring, until golden, ~{1-2%minutes}. Transfer
the sesame seeds to a small bowl.

Heat a glug of @oil{} in a #medium frying pan{} on a medium high heat. When hot,
add the tofu and fry for ~{2%minutes} per side until crispy all over,
~{8%minutes}. While the tofu fries, mix the @maple syrup{1} and half the
@soy sauce{25%ml} in a small bowl. Once the tofu is crispy add the soy and
maple syrup then cook, stirring frequently, until the sauce has reduced and the
tofu is glazed, ~{2-3%minutes}. Once cooked, remove the tofu from the pan to a
#bowl{}, cover with #foil{} and set aside. Wipe the pan clean.

Put the #frying pan{} back on a medium high heat, drizzle with @oil{}. When hot
add the tenderstem broccoli and stir fry until starting to brown,
~{2-3%minutes}. Add a splash of water, cover with a lid and steam fry until
the broccoli is tender, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Once tender add the
@ginger puree{1}, lime zest, garlic, chilli and pak choi. Stir fry until the
bok choy has wilted, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove the star anise from the rice and add
the rice and remaining soy sauce to the pan. Stir to combine. Season with a
pinch of salt and squeeze of lime juice if needed.

Share the stir fried rice and veg between your #bowls{}. Top with the maple soy
glazed tofu. Sprinkle over the sesame seeds and spring onion and serve with a
lime wedge on the side. Enjoy!

